snippet.title: Emporia Smart
snippet.description: Designed with seniors in mind, the Emporia Smart is an Android smartphone that packs a physical emergency call button, a stylus, and a minimalistic user interface.

snippet.title: Jonathan Schwartz: Oracle bungled its chance at mobile Java
snippet.description: Oracle could have innovated with Java instead of litigated, says CareZone co-founder and Sun's former CEO. Also: Why Amazon won at cloud computing, "Intel Inside" was a blip, and the Mac is back.

snippet.title: Doro PhoneEasy 622
snippet.description: At Mobile World Congress today, Doro launched its PhoneEasy 622, a flip phone with a 2-megapixel camera and video-recording capabilities, for the European market.

snippet.title: It's about time: RuneScape dumps Java for HTML5
snippet.description: commentary A widely used online game and longtime Java ally is ditching Oracle's security-plagued programming technology. Your move, Minecraft.

snippet.title: Apple updates Java, removes Java plugin
snippet.description: Apple is progressively moving away from supporting its in-house developed Java runtime for OS X.

snippet.title: Microsoft debuts developer preview of mysterious 'Project N'
snippet.description: "Project N," now officially christened ".Net Native" -- a new compiler for building faster Windows Store apps -- is available now as a developer preview.

snippet.title: IBM to take Watson mobile with developer challenge
snippet.description: Big Blue is funding a developer challenge to encourage mobile developers to come up with applications that use its intelligent cloud-based service Watson.

snippet.title: Install command line developer tools in OS X
snippet.description: If you need access to programming tools on your Mac, there are several ways to go about installing them.

snippet.title: Ep. 1249: Where we get the senior discount
snippet.description: A pedalocalypse will descend on New York this May when Bloomberg's Citi Bike Share plan comes to fruition. We'll weigh the pros and cons, plus Apple bikes, cell phone dial tones, a 94-year-old Tweeter, and more.

snippet.title: Windows Phone 8.1 features leaked by developer
snippet.description: What surprises await the next version of Microsoft's mobile OS? One person with access to the Software Development Kit reveals a few tidbits.
